twitter.text:
freeradius: As promised.  https://t.co/Go0DbAxou7

v4 now supports TACACS+ as an experimental protocol.
freeradius: FreeRADIUS defines yet another RADIUS standard.  https://t.co/pwzHphCtyd
freeradius: Big news next week.  No v4, but some major new functionality in the v4.0.x branch.
freeradius: v4 update.  Tested master / worker thread exchanging fake packets.  1M req/reply per second per thread.  The new network IO is scalable.
freeradius: Preliminary support for LuaJit via rlm_lua in v4.0.x.  Should be MUCH faster than other interpreted languages.
freeradius: The v4.0.x branch now supports sigtran for EAP-SIM.  i.e. SS7 integration.  Be warned, though, license issues apply!  Use at your own risk.
freeradius: Much of the "back end" stays the same.  Modules, config files, unlang, etc.  The only work left to do now is the "front end" networking.
freeradius: A good chunk of the version 4 implementation has already been done.  The unlang interpreter is now asynchronous.
freeradius: Version 4 design notes on the Wiki.  https://t.co/LTP4oByNNw  Pictures and schematics uploaded next week.
freeradius: Designing version 4.  Implementing version 4 from the ground up.  No memory copies.  Minimal system calls.  Goal 100K to 1M packets/s

stackoverflow.body:
I am using FreeRADIUS along with MySQL to authenticate users.

Users are saved in the radcheck table. User attributes are saved in the radreply table.

For example I have a user named Bob in the radcheck table.



Bob has a Session-Timeout value of 60 (1 minute) in the radreply table.



This all works fine. My problem is that RADIUS just re-authenticates Bob straight away. I assume this is because Bob still exists in the radcheck table.

Is there a way to remove Bob from the radcheck and radreply tables after the Session-Timeout time has been reached?
stackoverflow.title: FreeRADIUS - Delete user from database when session has expired

stackoverflow.body:
I faced with one issue, which I can't understand in Freeradius users file.
My goal is just authenticate external user "shad" with password "test".
I added line in /etc/raddb/users the following line:
shad    Cleartext-Password == "test"
Result was Reject. If I change "==" operator to ":=" Authentication is successful.
So my question is the following:
Why I can't use "==" operator while FreeRadius documentation tells:
"Attribute == Value
As a check item, it matches if the named attribute is present in the request, AND has the given value."

And one more question.
In some resourses I faced with such lines:
shad  Auth-Type := Local, User-Password == "test"
I tried and it doesn't work. Responce is Reject with log:
[pap] WARNING! No "known good" password found for the user.  Authentication may fail because of this.

Thank you in advance.
Best Regards.

i figured out, if you have your "azure ad" enabled service/host on your local network, for azure its working same as for local ad.
important to understand is, that you need to enable the required service so freeradius can connect to it. and just enabling it on public ip is not recommended, better create an (ipsec) tunnel to microsoft and enable the ad service on local ip.

stackoverflow.body:
Ok, you seem to be asking about two different problems. "login failed: RADIUS server is not responding" implies the authentication isn't working at all on the Mikrotik. At the same time, "mikrotik accounting is not passed" implies you are just not seeing accounting data from the Mikrotik. (Accounting doesn't happen unless Authentication and Authorization have been successful.) Here are a few things to check.


Be sure to specify the Src Address under Radius on the Mikrotik. This should be the IP address of the interface on your Mikrotik that is used to reach your radius server. You'd be shocked how many times RouterOS picks the wrong one when left to its own devices.
Some versions of RouterOS had the Timeout value set to an unreasonably low value under the Radius page. Set it to something comfortable like 5000 ms so a saturated circuit is less likely to prevent signin.
To make your accounting work, go to IP -> Hotspot -> Server Profiles and open up your profile. Make sure Accounting is checked and the interval is set to something like 5 or 10 minutes.
